<br />Trouble is that too many rips might be "like Metroid", especially on the MMC3 that uses smaller banks. Should we consider reverse engineering common NES music playback engines in order to make a version that uses the same instrument and sequence data but runs properly in a flat 32 KB memory space?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
